%N A066828 Numbers k that divide the average of prime(k-1) and prime(k+1).
%C A066828 Each cluster of candidates is about e (2.71828...) times as large as the previous one.
%e A066828 The average of prime(4) = 7 and prime(6) = 13 is 10, which is divisible by 5, so 5 is a term of the sequence.
%t A066828 a = 0; b = 1; c = 2; Do[ c = Prime[ n + 1 ]; If[ IntegerQ[ (a + c)/(2n) ], Print[ n ] ]; a = b; b = c, {n, 1, 2 10^9} ]
